oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Belfast scene
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of Belfast showing businesses and other buildings. Some of the buildings pictured are the warehouse of Robert William Starr, Robert William's store, a blacksmith, and the store belonging to Henry and Jasper McAdams. Train tracks are running across in the foreground and two young boys are standing on them.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
